{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/41814.I_Asimov", "title": "I. Asimov: A Memoir", "titleComplete": "I. Asimov: A Memoir", "description": "Arguably the greatest science fiction writer who ever lived, Isaac Asimov also possessed one of the most brilliant and original minds of our time. His accessible style and far-reaching interests in subjects ranging from science to humor to history earned him the nickname \"the Great Explainer.\" I. Asimov is his personal story\u2014vivid, open, and honest\u2014as only Asimov himself could tell it.Here is the story of the paradoxical genius who wrote of travel to the stars yet refused to fly in airplanes; who imagined alien universes and vast galactic civilizations while staying home to write; who compulsively authored more than 470 books yet still found the time to share his ideas with some of the great minds of our century. Here are his wide-ranging thoughts and sharp-eyed observations on everything from religion to politics, love and divorce, friendship and Hollywood, fame and mortality. Here, too, is a riveting behind-the-scenes look at the varied personalities\u2014Campbell, Ellison, Heinlein, Clarke, del Rey, Silverberg, and others\u2014who along with Asimov helped shape science fiction.As unique and irrepressible as the man himself, I. Asimov\u00a0is the candid memoir of an incomparable talent who entertained readers for nearly half a century and whose work will surely endure into the future he so vividly envisioned.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1386922885i/41814.jpg", "genres": ["History", "Hugo Awards", "Writing", "Biography", "Memoir", "Literature", "Biography Memoir", "Science", "Autobiography", "Nonfiction"], "asin": "055356997X", "isbn": "055356997X", "isbn13": "9780553569971", "publisher": "Bantam", "series": ["The Autobiography of Isaac Asimov"], "author": ["Isaac Asimov"], "publishDate": 788947200000, "characters": ["Isaac Asimov"], "ratingHistogram": [136, 168, 531, 1173, 1336], "ratingsCount": 3344, "reviewsCount": 176, "numPages": 578, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Hugo Award", "awardedAt": 788947200000, "category": "Best Non-Fiction Book", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Locus Award", "awardedAt": 788947200000, "category": "Best Non-Fiction", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/22743914-a-tept-ndu-i-pe-barbari", "title": "A\u0219tept\u00e2ndu-i pe barbari", "titleComplete": "A\u0219tept\u00e2ndu-i pe barbari", "description": "La peste 30 de ani de la apari\u0163ie, romanul A\u015ftept\u00e2ndu-i pe barbari a r\u0103mas \u00een con\u015ftiin\u0163a public\u0103 \u015fi continu\u0103 s\u0103 influen\u0163eze alte forme ale artei, cum ar fi opera omonim\u0103 din 2005 semnat\u0103 de compozitorul Philip Glass. A fost \u00eencununat cu James Tait Black Memorial Prize, Geoffrey Faber Memorial Prize \u015fi Central News Agency Prize. Dup\u0103 ce J.M. Coetzee a c\u00e2\u015ftigat Premiul Nobel pentru literatur\u0103 \u00een 2003, acest roman a fost inclus de Penguin Books \u00een prestigioasa serie \u201eGreat Books of the 20th Century\u201c.Magistratul nu are nume, ci doar o misiune: trebuie sa imparta dreptatea intr-un fort situat departe de inima Imperiului. Iar acest fort se afla, se spune, sub amenintarea barbarilor. Nimeni nu stie precis cum arata si cum se comporta acestia. Conteaza doar veghea perpetua si indeplinirea datoriei fata de Imperiu. Dar cand in fort isi face aparitia colonelul Joll, purtatorul trufas al ordinelor de la centru, contururile ferme ale lucrurilor si certitudinile omului legii incep sa se estompeze. Colonelul da dovada de cruzime gratuita, de inflexibilitate criminala, de dispret suveran fata de semeni. Incet-incet, il descoperim si pe barbar: el nu este vanatorul care depinde de toanele naturii sau cersetorul momit de aburii unei cafele, ci tocmai eroul civilizator in epoleti, instalat in voluptatea torturii si venit sa-i convinga cu biciul pe cei care nu se supun orbeste unor legi absurde.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1405772273i/22743914.jpg", "genres": ["Literary Fiction", "Novels", "Nobel Prize", "Historical Fiction", "South Africa", "Literature", "African Literature", "Classics", "Fiction", "Africa"], "asin": "9736897567", "isbn": "9736897567", "isbn13": "9789736897566", "publisher": "Humanitas Fiction", "author": ["Michaela Niculescu", "J.M. Coetzee"], "publishDate": 1404198000000, "characters": ["The Magistrate"], "ratingHistogram": [522, 1792, 6929, 12887, 9848], "ratingsCount": 31978, "reviewsCount": 2540, "numPages": 232, "language": "Romanian", "awards": [{"name": "James Tait Black Memorial Prize", "awardedAt": 315561600000, "category": "Fiction", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Philip K. Dick Award", "awardedAt": 410256000000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "CNA Literary Award", "awardedAt": 315561600000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Geoffrey Faber Memorial Prize", "awardedAt": 347184000000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/88442.Austerlitz", "title": "Austerlitz", "titleComplete": "Austerlitz", "description": "Austerlitz, the internationally acclaimed masterpiece by \u201cone of the most gripping writers imaginable\u201d (The New York Review of Books), is the story of a man\u2019s search for the answer to his life\u2019s central riddle. A small child when he comes to England on a Kindertransport in the summer of 1939, one Jacques Austerlitz is told nothing of his real family by the Welsh Methodist minister and his wife who raise him. When he is a much older man, the fleeting memories return to him, and obeying an instinct he only dimly understands, he follows their trail back to the world he left behind a half century before. There, faced with the void at the heart of twentieth-century Europe, he struggles to rescue his heritage from oblivion.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1516499623i/88442.jpg", "genres": ["Holocaust", "Fiction", "Novels", "Historical Fiction", "German Literature", "Literature", "Classics", "Germany", "Historical", "War"], "asin": "0140297995", "isbn": "0140297995", "isbn13": "9780140297997", "publisher": "Penguin Books Ltd", "author": ["Anthea Bell", "W.G. Sebald"], "publishDate": 1025766000000, "characters": ["Jacques Austerlitz"], "places": ["Prague (Praha)", "Paris", "Mari\u00e1nsk\u00e9 L\u00e1zn\u011b", "Antwerp", "London, England", "Terez\u00edn"], "ratingHistogram": [721, 1504, 3883, 6794, 8946], "ratingsCount": 21848, "reviewsCount": 2009, "numPages": 415, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Independent Foreign Fiction Prize", "awardedAt": 1009872000000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"name": "National Book Critics Circle Award", "awardedAt": 978336000000, "category": "Fiction", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Bremer Literaturpreis", "awardedAt": 1009872000000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Jewish Quarterly-Wingate Prize"