{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/11105574-iubiri-caraghioase", "title": "Iubiri caraghioase", "titleComplete": "Iubiri caraghioase", "description": "Iubirea este pentru Milan Kundera altceva decat blanda visare sau suspin abisal, ceva mult mai palpabil, \u201eepidermic\u201c aproape. Nu maladive fantasme, nu obscure pulsiuni ii imping pe eroii nuvelelor sale unul catre altul: in doi, nu e loc de subtile ocoluri si de inavuabile complexe; totul se reduce la expresia cea mai brutala a esentialului. Cu nespusa luciditate si cu enorma ironie, Kundera dezvaluie resorturile cotidiene ale relatiei de cuplu, care sfarsesc prin a provoca un imens hohot de ras. Un ras izbavitor, fiindca sub tribulatiile erotice ale personajelor isi arata intotdeauna chipul una dintre meschinele strategii de disimulare si supravietuire ale omului, aceea care masoara adevarata dimensiune a esecului sau.Cuprins:Nimeni nu va radeMarul de aur al dorintei eterneFalsul autostopSimpozionulMortii varstnici sa cedeze locul mortilor tineriDoctorul Havel dupa douazeci de aniEduard si Dumnezeu", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1348862142i/11105574.jpg", "genres": ["Philosophy", "Novels", "Short Stories", "Romance", "Czech Literature", "Literature", "Classics", "Fiction", "20th Century", "Contemporary"], "isbn": "9735013673", "publisher": "Humanitas", "author": ["Jean Grosu", "Milan Kundera"], "publishDate": 1136102400000, "ratingHistogram": [445, 1831, 8724, 13572, 8354], "ratingsCount": 32926, "reviewsCount": 2110, "numPages": 268, "language": "Romanian"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/616035.The_Necklace_and_Other_Tales", "title": "The Necklace and Other Tales", "titleComplete": "The Necklace and Other Tales", "description": "Includes \n  The Necklace, Butterball, The Tellier House, On the Water, Mademoiselle Fifi, The Mask, The Inn, A Day in the Country, The Hand, The Jewels, The Model, The Entity (The Horla)\nThese stories\u2014poignant scrutinies of social pretension, wicked tales of lust and love, and harrowing examinations of terror and madness\u2014display the full genius of Guy de Maupassant in an enthralling new translation by Joachim Neugroschel. They reveal Maupassant\u2019s remarkable range, his technical perfection, his sexual realism, and his ability to create whole worlds and sum up intricate universes of feeling in a few pages", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1628138269i/616035.jpg", "genres": ["France", "French Literature", "School", "Short Stories", "19th Century", "Literature", "Classic Literature", "Classics", "Fiction", "Read For School"], "asin": "0375757171", "isbn": "0375757171", "isbn13": "9780375757174", "publisher": "Modern Library", "author": ["Adam Gopnik", "Joachim Neugroschel", "Guy de Maupassant"], "publishDate": 1068537600000, "ratingHistogram": [221, 902, 4372, 6687, 5899], "ratingsCount": 18081, "reviewsCount": 573, "numPages": 224, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/4671.The_Great_Gatsby", "title": "The Great Gatsby", "titleComplete": "The Great Gatsby", "description": "The Great Gatsby, F. Scott Fitzgerald's third book, stands as the supreme achievement of his career. This exemplary novel of the Jazz Age has been acclaimed by generations of readers. The story of the fabulously wealthy Jay Gatsby and his love for the beautiful Daisy Buchanan, of lavish parties on Long Island at a time when The New York Times noted \"gin was the national drink and sex the national obsession,\" it is an exquisitely crafted tale of America in the 1920s.The Great Gatsby is one of the great classics of twentieth-century literature.(from the back cover)", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1490528560i/4671.jpg", "genres": ["High School", "School", "Novels", "Historical Fiction", "Romance", "Literature", "Classics", "Fiction", "Historical", "Read For School"], "publisher": "Scribner", "author": ["F. Scott Fitzgerald"], "publishDate": -1420041600000, "characters": ["Myrtle Wilson", "Jordan Baker", "Meyer Wolfsheim", "Tom Buchanan", "George Wilson", "Daisy Buchanan", "Nick Carraway", "Jay Gatsby"], "places": ["New York (State)", "New York City, New York", "The United States of America", "Long Island, New York"], "ratingHistogram": [146679, 337617, 1115349, 1760588, 1843014], "ratingsCount": 5203247, "reviewsCount": 103932, "numPages": 180, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Grammy Award", "awardedAt": 1041408000000, "category": "Best Spoken Word Album", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Long Island Reads", "awardedAt": 1009872000000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/175324.Double_Star", "title": "Double Star", "titleComplete": "Double Star", "description": "One minute, down and out actor Lorenzo Smythe was \u2014 as usual \u2014 in a bar, drinking away his troubles as he watched his career go down the tubes. Then a space pilot bought him a drink, and the next thing Smythe knew, he was shanghaied to Mars.Suddenly he found himself agreeing to the most difficult role of his career: impersonating an important politician who had been kidnapped. Peace with the Martians was at stake \u2014 failure to pull off the act could result in interplanetary war. And Smythe's own life was on the line \u2014 for if he wasn't assassinated, there was always the possibility that he might be trapped in his new role forever!", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327984434i/175324.jpg", "genres": ["Science Fiction Fantasy", "Hugo Awards", "Science Fiction", "Novels", "Fantasy", "Audiobook", "Classics", "Fiction", "Speculative Fiction", "Politics"], "asin": "0345330137", "isbn": "0345330137", "isbn13": "9780345330130", "publisher": "Del Rey", "author": ["Robert A. Heinlein"], "publishDate": 529484400000, "characters": ["Lorenzo Smythe"], "ratingHistogram": [227, 1092, 6034, 8801, 6833], "ratingsCount": 22987, "reviewsCount": 969, "numPages": 243, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Hugo Award", "awardedAt": -441820800000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Locus Award", "awardedAt": 536486400000, "category": "All-Time Best SF Novel", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6334.Never_Let_Me_Go", "title": "Never Let Me Go", "titleComplete": "Never Let Me Go", "description": "Hailsham seems like a pleasant English boarding school, far from the influences of the city. Its students are well tended and supported, trained in art and literature, and become just the sort of people the world wants them to be. But, curiously, they are taught nothing of the outside world and are allowed little contact with it.Within the grounds of Hailsham, Kathy grows from schoolgirl to young woman, but it\u2019s only when she and her friends Ruth and Tommy leave the safe grounds of the school (as they always knew they would) that they realize the full truth of what Hailsham is.Never Let Me Go breaks through the boundaries of the literary novel. It is a gripping mystery, a beautiful love story, and also a scathing critique of human arrogance and a moral examination of how we treat the vulnerable and different in our society. In exploring the themes of memory and the impact of the past, Ishiguro takes on the idea of a possible future to create his most moving and powerful book to date.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1353048590i/6334.jpg", "genres": ["Literary Fiction", "Science Fiction", "Adult", "Novels", "Romance", "Dystopia", "Literature", "Classics", "Fiction", "Contemporary"], "asin": "1400078776", "publisher": "Vintage Books ", "author": ["Kazuo Ishiguro"], "publishDate": 1283238000000, "characters": ["Tommy D.", "Kathy H.", "Ruth (Never Let Me Go)"], "places": ["Hailsham", "United Kingdom", "England"], "ratingHistogram": [16794, 50411, 160745, 253347, 206526], "ratingsCount": 687823, "reviewsCount": 52184, "numPages": 288, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Booker Prize", "awardedAt": 1104566400000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Locus Award", "awardedAt": 1136102400000, "category": "Best SF Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"nam