{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/84737.Zeno_s_Conscience", "title": "Zeno's Conscience", "titleComplete": "Zeno's Conscience", "description": "Long hailed as a seminal work of modernism in the tradition of Joyce and Kafka, and now available in a supple new English translation, Italo Svevo\u2019s charming and splendidly idiosyncratic novel conducts readers deep into one hilariously hyperactive and endlessly self-deluding mind. The mind in question belongs to one Zeno Cosini, a neurotic Italian businessman who is writing his confessions at the behest of his psychiatrist. Here are Zeno\u2019s interminable attempts to quit smoking, his courtship of the beautiful yet unresponsive Ada, his unexpected\u2013and unexpectedly happy\u2013marriage to Ada\u2019s homely sister Augusta, and his affair with a shrill-voiced aspiring singer. Relating these misadventures with wry wit and irony, and a perspicacity at once unblinking and compassionate, Zeno\u2019s Conscience is a miracle of psychological realism.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1634559146i/84737.jpg", "genres": ["Italian Literature", "Italy", "Psychology", "Literary Fiction", "Novels", "School", "Literature", "Classics", "Fiction", "20th Century"], "asin": "0375727760", "isbn": "0375727760", "isbn13": "9780375727764", "publisher": "Vintage", "author": ["Beryl de Zoete", "Claudio Carini", "Italo Svevo", "William Weaver", "Michael Hoffman"], "publishDate": 1044345600000, "characters": ["Zeno Cosini"], "places": ["Italy", "Trieste"], "ratingHistogram": [763, 2166, 6726, 9680, 7360], "ratingsCount": 26695, "reviewsCount": 1266, "numPages": 437, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Premi Cr\u00edtica Serra d'Or de Traducci\u00f3", "awardedAt": 504950400000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/12287.Endgame", "title": "Endgame", "titleComplete": "Endgame", "description": "Samuel Beckett was awarded the Nobel Prize for Literature in 1969; his literary output of plays, novels, stories, and poetry has earned him an uncontested place as one of the greatest writers of our time. Endgame, originally written in French and translated into English by Beckett himself, is now considered by many critics to be his greatest single work. A pinnacle of Beckett's characteristic raw minimalism, it is a pure and devastating distillation of the human essence in the face of approaching death.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1452534163i/12287.jpg", "genres": ["Plays", "Ireland", "France", "Irish Literature", "Literature", "Theatre", "Classics", "Drama", "Fiction", "20th Century"], "asin": "0571070671", "isbn": "0571070671", "isbn13": "9780571070671", "publisher": "Faber and Faber", "author": ["Samuel Beckett"], "publishDate": 599644800000, "characters": ["Nell", "Clov", "Hamm", "Nagg"], "ratingHistogram": [849, 1844, 4902, 7450, 6692], "ratingsCount": 21737, "reviewsCount": 1212, "numPages": 60, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Obie", "awardedAt": -378662400000, "category": "Best Foreign Play", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/15823480-anna-karenina", "title": "Anna Karenina", "titleComplete": "Anna Karenina", "description": "Acclaimed by many as the world's greatest novel, Anna Karenina provides a vast panorama of contemporary life in Russia and of humanity in general. In it Tolstoy uses his intense imaginative insight to create some of the most memorable characters in all of literature. Anna is a sophisticated woman who abandons her empty existence as the wife of Karenin and turns to Count Vronsky to fulfil her passionate nature - with tragic consequences. Levin is a reflection of Tolstoy himself, often expressing the author's own views and convictions.Throughout, Tolstoy points no moral, merely inviting us not to judge but to watch. As Rosemary Edmonds comments, 'He leaves the shifting patterns of the kaleidoscope to bring home the meaning of the brooding words following the title, 'Vengeance is mine, and I will repay.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1546091617i/15823480.jpg", "genres": ["Russia", "Novels", "19th Century", "Historical Fiction", "Romance", "Literature", "Classics", "Fiction", "Historical", "Russian Literature"], "publisher": "Vintage", "author": ["Louise Maude", "Lev Tolstoj", "Aylmer Maude", "Dieter Wellershoff", "L\u00e9on Tolsto\u00ef", "Bruno Goetz", "Leo Tolstoy"], "publishDate": 1350370800000, "characters": ["Princess Ekaterina \"Kitty\" Aleksandrovna Shcherbatskaya", "Count Aleksei Kirillovich Vronsky", "Prince Stepan \"Stiva\" Arkadyevitch Oblonsky", "Konstantin \"Kostya\" Dmitrievitch Levin", "Anna Arkadyevna Karenina"], "places": ["Russia"], "ratingHistogram": [19677, 42312, 143217, 276394, 362224], "ratingsCount": 843824, "reviewsCount": 35088, "numPages": 964, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Premio literatura rusa en Espa\u00f1a", "awardedAt": 1325404800000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Read Russia Prize", "awardedAt": 1