{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/15830401-generalul-armatei-moarte", "title": "Generalul armatei moarte", "titleComplete": "Generalul armatei moarte", "description": "In furtunosii ani \u201960, un general italian si un preot sint trimisi in Albania sa aduca in patrie ramasitele soldatilor morti in al Doilea Razboi Mondial. Pe masura ce timpul trece si osemintele celor morti se aduna, cei doi vor ajunge sa-si descopere adevaratele instincte. Daca la inceputul misiunii generalul pare minat de un exacerbat simt al datoriei, incetul cu incetul, odata cu evolutia romanului, manifestarile inumane, cruzimea si izbucnirile paranoice vor lua locul unei masti bine construite de-a lungul unei vieti.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1345068022i/15830401.jpg", "genres": ["Novels", "Historical Fiction", "Albanian Literature", "20th Century", "Literature", "Classics", "World War II", "Fiction", "Historical", "War"], "asin": "9734622846", "isbn": "9734622846", "isbn13": "9789734622849", "publisher": "Polirom", "author": ["Ismail Kadare", "Marius Dobrescu"], "publishDate": 1293868800000, "places": ["Albania"], "ratingHistogram": [40, 191, 883, 1649, 1495], "ratingsCount": 4258, "reviewsCount": 355, "numPages": 228, "language": "Romanian"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/87280.Too_Loud_a_Solitude", "title": "Too Loud a Solitude", "titleComplete": "Too Loud a Solitude", "description": "TOO LOUD A SOLITUDE is a tender and funny story of Ha\u0148\u0165a - a man who has lived in a Czech police state - for 35 years, working as compactor of wastepaper and books. In the process of compacting, he has acquired an education so unwitting he can't quite tell which of his thoughts are his own and which come from his books. He has rescued many from jaws of hydraulic press and now his house is filled to the rooftops. Destroyer of the written word, he is also its perpetrator.But when a new automatic press makes his job redundant there's only one thing he can do - go down with his ship.This is an eccentric romp celebrating the indestructability- against censorship, political opression etc - of the written word.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1359996651i/87280.jpg", "genres": ["Philosophy", "Literary Fiction", "Novella", "Novels", "Books About Books", "Czech Literature", "Literature", "Classics", "Fiction", "20th Century"], "asin": "0349102627", "isbn": "0349102627", "isbn13": "9780349102627", "publisher": "Abacus", "author": ["Michael Henry Heim", "Bohumil Hrabal"], "publishDate": 725875200000, "characters": ["Ha\u0148\u0165a"], "places": ["Prague (Praha)"], "ratingHistogram": [567, 1399, 4274, 7804, 8490], "ratingsCount": 22534, "reviewsCount": 2841, "numPages": 112, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/414999.Childhood_s_End", "title": "Childhood\u2019s End", "titleComplete": "Childhood\u2019s End", "description": "The Overlords appeared suddenly over every city\u2014intellectually, technologically, and militarily superior to humankind. Benevolent, they made few demands: unify earth, eliminate poverty, and end war. With little rebellion, humankind agreed, and a golden age began. But at what cost? With the advent of peace, man ceases to strive for creative greatness, and a malaise settles over the human race. To those who resist, it becomes evident that the Overlords have an agenda of their own. As civilization approaches the crossroads, will the Overlords spell the end for humankind . . . or the beginning?", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1320552628i/414999.jpg", "genres": ["Aliens", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "Science Fiction", "Novels", "Fantasy", "Dystopia", "Audiobook", "Classics", "Fiction", "Speculative Fiction"], "publisher": "Del Rey Books", "author": ["Arthur C. Clarke"], "publishDate": 547801200000, "characters": ["Jan Rodricks", "Rikki Stormgren", "Karellen"], "ratingHistogram": [1653, 5587, 28034, 60128, 63272], "ratingsCount": 158674, "reviewsCount": 7289, "numPages": 224, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Retro Hugo Award", "awardedAt": 1072944000000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/9334792-despre-dragoste-i-al-i-demoni", "title": "Despre dragoste \u015fi al\u0163i demoni", "titleComplete": "Despre dragoste \u015fi al\u0163i demoni", "description": "In 1942, intr-o manastire din America Latina sunt scoase la lumina ramasitele lumesti ale unei adolescente, Sierva Maria de Todos Los Angeles. Splendida ei podoaba capilara masoara douazeci si doi de metri lungime... Sa fie oare aceasta descoperire fructul imaginatiei inflacarate a autorului? Reala sau fictiva, ea reprezinta punctul de plecare al unei inedite povesti de dragoste, desfasurate pe fundalul pitoresc si decadent al Cartagenei, la mijlocul secolului al XVIII-lea. Sierva Maria este muscata la varsta de douazeci de ani de un caine. Banuind-o de turbare sau ca ar fi posedata de diavol, Inchizitia o trimite la o manastire, unde, alaturi de exorcistul ei, Don Cayetano Delaura, traieste o pasiune nebuna, distructiva si, prin urmare, blestemata... Prin aceasta capodopera situata la cumpana dintre istorie si legenda, misticism si erotism, Gabriel Garcia Marquez depaseste granitele realismului magic. Poezia si maiestria stilului sau transforma aici scena magicianului aventurier intr-un minunat iconostas baroc.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1300122029i/9334792.jpg", "genres": ["Magical Realism", "Spanish Literature", "Novels", "Historical Fiction", "Latin American", "Romance", "Latin American Literature", "Literature", "Classics", "Fiction"], "asin": "9735769883", "isbn": "9735769883", "isbn13": "9789735769888", "publisher": "RAO", "author": ["Gabriel Garc\u00eda M\u00e1rquez"], "publishDate": 1136102400000, "characters": ["Martina Laborde", "Josefa Miranda", "Sierva Mar\u00eda", "don Toribio de C\u00e1ceres y Virtudes", "Abrenuncio", "Bernarda Cabrera", "Dulce Olivia", "Cayetano Delaura", "don Ignacio"], "places": ["Colombia"], "ratingHistogram": [823, 3478, 17032, 30318, 23961], "ra