{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/31548.Of_Human_Bondage", "title": "Of Human Bondage", "titleComplete": "Of Human Bondage", "description": "From a tormented orphan with a clubfoot, Philip Carey grows into an impressionable young man with a voracious appetite for adventure and knowledge. His cravings take him to Paris at age eighteen to try his hand at art, then back to London to study medicine. But even so, nothing can sate his nagging hunger for experience. Then he falls obsessively in love, embarking on a disastrous relationship that will change his life forever.\u2026Marked by countless similarities to Maugham\u2019s own life, his masterpiece is \u201cnot an autobiography,\u201d as the author himself once contended, \u201cbut an autobiographical novel; fact and fiction are inexorably mingled; the emotions are my own.\u201d", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1386924695i/31548.jpg", "genres": ["Coming Of Age", "Literary Fiction", "British Literature", "Novels", "Historical Fiction", "Romance", "Literature", "Classics", "Fiction", "20th Century"], "asin": "0451530179", "isbn": "0451530179", "isbn13": "9780451530172", "publisher": "Signet", "author": ["W. Somerset Maugham", "Maeve Binchy", "Benjamin DeMott"], "publishDate": 1167724800000, "characters": ["Thorpe Athelny", "Cronshaw", "Fanny Price (Of Human Bondage)", "Emily Wilkinson", "Louisa Carey", "Dr. Tyrell", "Norah Nesbit", "Ruth Chalice", "Mildred Rogers", "Betty Athelny", "Dr. South", "Hayward", "Harry Griffiths", "Frederick Lawson", "Philip Carey", "Sally Athelny"], "places": ["Blackstable, Kent, England", "Brighton and Hove, Sussex, England", "Paris", "England", "London, England", "Heidelberg"], "ratingHistogram": [1031, 2508, 8833, 19550, 24989], "ratingsCount": 56911, "reviewsCount": 4036, "numPages": 684, "language": "English"}
