{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/22590.Ubik", "title": "Ubik", "titleComplete": "Ubik", "description": "Glen Runciter est\u00e1 muerto. \u00bfO lo est\u00e1n todos los dem\u00e1s? Lo que es seguro es que alguien ha muerto en una explosi\u00f3n organizada por los competidores de Runciter. De hecho, sus empleados asisten a un funeral. Pero durante el duelo comienzan a recibir mensajes descorcentantes, e incluso morbosos, de su jefe. Y el mundo a su alrededor comienza a desmoronarse de un modo que sugiere que a ellos tampoco les queda mucho tiempo. Esta mordaz comedia metaf\u00edsica de muerte y salvaci\u00f3n (que podr\u00e1 llevar un c\u00f3modo envase) es un tour de force de amenaza paranoica y comedia absurda, en la cual los muertos ofrecen consejos comerciales, compran su siguiente reencarnaci\u00f3n y corren el riesgo continuo de volver a morir.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327995569i/22590.jpg", "genres": ["Science Fiction Fantasy", "Mystery", "Science Fiction", "Novels", "Fantasy", "Audiobook", "Classics", "American", "Fiction", "Speculative Fiction"], "asin": "8498000831", "isbn": "8498000831", "isbn13": "9788498000832", "publisher": "La factor\u00eda de ideas", "author": ["Philip K. Dick"], "publishDate": 1100073600000, "characters": ["Wendy Wright", "Jory", "Stanton Mick", "Don Denny", "Ella Runciter", "Glen Runciter", "Joe Chip", "Patricia Conley", "Al Hammond"], "ratingHistogram": [1237, 4177, 18721, 41127, 42207], "ratingsCount": 107469, "reviewsCount": 6173, "numPages": 288, "language": "Spanish; Castilian"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/612188.Memories_Dreams_Reflections", "title": "Memories, Dreams, Reflections", "titleComplete": "Memories, Dreams, Reflections", "description": "In the spring of 1957, when he was eighty-one years old, C. G. Jung undertook the telling of his life story. At regular intervals he had conversations with his colleague and friend Aniela Jaff\u00e9, and collaborated with her in the preparation of the text based on these talks. On occasion, he was moved to write entire chapters of the book in his own hand, and he continued to work on the final stages of the manuscript until shortly before his death on June 6, 1961.This edition of Memories, Dreams, Reflections includes Jung's VII Sermones ad Mortuos. It is a fully corrected edition.\u00a0From the Trade Paperback edition.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1348081175i/612188.jpg", "genres": ["Science", "Psychology", "History", "Spirituality", "Psychoanalysis", "Memoir", "Autobiography", "Philosophy", "Biography", "Nonfiction"], "asin": "0679723951", "isbn": "0679723951", "isbn13": "9780679723950", "publisher": "Vintage", "author": ["Clara Winston", "C.G. Jung", "Richard Winston", "Aniela Jaff\u00e9"], "publishDate": 607420800000, "characters": ["Carl Jung"], "ratingHistogram": [1080, 1408, 4759, 10491, 16340], "ratingsCount": 34078, "reviewsCount": 1161, "numPages": 430, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/14817.A_Scanner_Darkly", "title": "A Scanner Darkly", "titleComplete": "A Scanner Darkly", "description": "Substance D is not known as Death for nothing. It is the most toxic drug ever to find its way on to the streets of LA. It destroys the links between the brain's two hemispheres, causing, first, disorientation and then complete and irreversible brain damage.The undercover narcotics agent who calls himself Bob Arctor is desperate to discover the ultimate source of supply. But to find any kind of lead he has to pose as a user and, inevitably, without realising what is happening, Arctor is soon as addicted as the junkies he works among...", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388737865i/14817.jpg", "genres": ["Science Fiction Fantasy", "Science Fiction", "Novels", "Fantasy", "Dystopia", "Classics", "American", "Cyberpunk", "Fiction", "Speculative Fiction"], "asin": "057507681X", "isbn": "057507681X", "isbn13": "9780575076815", "publisher": "Gollancz", "author": ["Philip K. Dick"], "publishDate": 1155798000000, "characters": ["Ernie Luckman", "Donna Hawthorne", "Bob Arctor", "Jim Barris", "Charles Freck"], "places": ["Los Angeles, California", "Anaheim, California", "Santa Ana, California"], "ratingHistogram": [1664, 4695, 19498, 39469, 36323], "ratingsCount": 101649, "reviewsCount": 4160, "numPages": 219, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Locus Award", "awardedAt": 252489600000, "category": "Best SF Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "British Science Fiction Association Award", "awardedAt": 252489600000, "category": "Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "John W. Campbell Memorial Award", "awardedAt": 252489600000, "category": "Best Science Fiction Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Graoully d'Or", "awardedAt": 284025600000, "category": "Roman \u00e9tranger", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "T\u00e4htivaeltaja Award", "awardedAt": 662716800000, "category": nu