{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/5470.1984", "title": "1984", "titleComplete": "1984", "description": "The year 1984 has come and gone, but George Orwell's prophetic, nightmarish vision in 1949 of the world we were becoming is timelier than ever. 1984 is still the great modern classic of \"negative utopia\"\u2014a startlingly original and haunting novel that creates an imaginary world that is completely convincing, from the first sentence to the last four words. No one can deny the novel's hold on the imaginations of whole generations, or the power of its admonitions\u2014a power that seems to grow, not lessen, with the passage of time.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1348990566i/5470.jpg", "genres": ["Adult", "Science Fiction", "Novels", "School", "Fantasy", "Dystopia", "Literature", "Classics", "Fiction", "Politics"], "publisher": "New American Library", "author": ["George Orwell"], "publishDate": -615484800000, "characters": ["Winston Smith", "Julia", "Tom Parsons", "Big Brother", "O'Brien", "Syme", "Emmanuel Goldstein", "Mr. Charrington"], "ratingHistogram": [93693, 174485, 649035, 1489660, 2156455], "ratingsCount": 4563328, "reviewsCount": 114067, "numPages": 328, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Prometheus Hall of Fame Award", "awardedAt": 441792000000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Audie Award", "awardedAt": 1672560000000, "category": "Audio Drama", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/16631.Steppenwolf", "title": "Steppenwolf", "titleComplete": "Steppenwolf", "description": "Steppenwolf is a poetical self-portrait of a man who felt himself to be half-human and half-wolf. This Faust-like and magical story is evidence of Hesse's searching philosophy and extraordinary sense of humanity as he tells of the humanization of a middle-aged misanthrope. Yet his novel can also be seen as a plea for rigorous self-examination and an indictment of the intellectual hypocrisy of the period. As Hesse himself remarked, \"Of all my books Steppenwolf is the one that was more often and more violently misunderstood than any of the others\".", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1389332672i/16631.jpg", "genres": ["Psychology", "Fiction", "Literary Fiction", "Novels", "German Literature", "Literature", "Classics", "Germany", "Philosophy", "20th Century"], "asin": "0140282580", "isbn": "0140282580", "isbn13": "9780140282580", "publisher": "Penguin", "author": ["Basil Creighton", "Hermann Hesse"], "publishDate": 915177600000, "characters": ["Pablo Soler", "Hermine", "Maria", "Harry Haller"], "ratingHistogram": [2581, 8275, 31044, 63194, 79119], "ratingsCount": 184213, "reviewsCount": 8057, "numPages": 256, "language": "English"}
