{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6218281-the-sweetness-at-the-bottom-of-the-pie", "title": "The Sweetness at the Bottom of the Pie", "titleComplete": "The Sweetness at the Bottom of the Pie (Flavia de Luce, #1)", "description": "It is the summer of 1950\u2013and at the once-grand mansion of Buckshaw, young Flavia de Luce, an aspiring chemist with a passion for poison, is intrigued by a series of inexplicable events: A dead bird is found on the doorstep, a postage stamp bizarrely pinned to its beak. Then, hours later, Flavia finds a man lying in the cucumber patch and watches him as he takes his dying breath.For Flavia, who is both appalled and delighted, life begins in earnest when murder comes to Buckshaw. \u201cI wish I could say I was afraid, but I wasn\u2019t. Quite the contrary. This was by far the most interesting thing that had ever happened to me in my entire life.\u201d", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388187001i/6218281.jpg", "genres": ["Crime", "Fiction", "Adult", "British Literature", "Historical Fiction", "Audiobook", "Mystery Thriller", "Young Adult", "Mystery", "Historical"], "asin": "0385342306", "isbn": "0385342306", "isbn13": "9780385342308", "publisher": "Delacorte Press", "series": ["Flavia de Luce "], "author": ["Alan Bradley"], "publishDate": 1240902000000, "characters": ["Tully Stoker", "Ned Cropper", "Frank Pemberton", "Mrs. Mullet", "Horace Bonepenny", "Flavia de Luce", "Inspector Hewitt", "Dogger", "Colonel de Luce", "Bob Stanley", "Daphne de Luce", "Ophelia de Luce", "Mary Stoker"], "places": ["Bishop's Lacey, England", "England"], "ratingHistogram": [4565, 11351, 40990, 64335, 47102], "ratingsCount": 168343, "reviewsCount": 18192, "numPages": 374, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Barry Award", "awardedAt": 1262332800000, "category": "Best First Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Macavity Award", "awardedAt": 1262332800000, "category": "Best First M