{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/9917996-salem-s-lot", "title": "'Salem's Lot", "titleComplete": "'Salem's Lot", "description": "'Salem's Lot is a small New England town with white clapboard houses, tree-lined streets, and solid church steeples. That summer in 'Salem's Lot was a summer of home-coming and return; spring burned out and the land lying dry, crackling underfoot. Late that summer, Ben Mears returned to 'Salem's Lot hoping to cast out his own devils... and found instead a new unspeakable horror.A stranger had also come to the Lot, a stranger with a secret as old as evil, a secret that would wreak irreparable harm on those he touched and in turn on those they loved.All would be changed forever\u2014Susan, whose love for Ben could not protect her; Father Callahan, the bad priest who put his eroded faith to one last test; and Mark, a young boy who sees his fantasy world become reality and ironically proves the best equipped to handle the relentless nightmare of 'Salem's Lot.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1708568369i/9917996.jpg", "genres": ["Mystery", "Adult", "Fantasy", "Thriller", "Vampires", "Supernatural", "Audiobook", "Fiction", "Paranormal", "Horror"], "asin": "0307743675", "publisher": "Anchor", "author": ["Stephen King"], "publishDate": 1324972800000, "characters": ["Richard Throckett Straker", "Mark Petrie", "Joe Crane", "Tookey", "Sonny James", "Larry McLeod", "Harriet Durham", "Father Donald Callahan", "Miss Coogan", "Matt Burke", "Dud Rogers", "Charles Boone", "Cynthia Stowens", "Hal Griffen", "Royal Snow", "Weasel Craig", "Benjamin Mears", "June Petrie", "Dr James Cody", "Nolly Gardener", "Mike Ryerson", "Danny Glick", "Larry Crockett", "Susan Norton", "Loretta Starcher", "Buddy Bascomb"], "places": ["Maine", "Jerusalem's Lot, Maine"], "ratingHistogram": [4833, 18570, 92807, 166678, 169850], "ratingsCount": 452738, "reviewsCount": 17900, "numPages": 653, "language"