{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/2161329.Profesor_Wilczur", "title": "Profesor Wilczur", "titleComplete": "Profesor Wilczur", "description": "Ci\u0105g dalszy los\u00f3w s\u0142awnego chirurga Rafa\u0142a Wilczura, znanego czytelnikom z powie\u015bci \"Znachor\". Po odzyskaniu pami\u0119ci profesor Wilczur wraca do pracy w warszawskiej prywatnej klinice, ale ju\u017c nie mo\u017ce znale\u017a\u0107 sobie miejsca w dawnym \u015brodowisku. Rozczarowany wielkim \u015bwiatem, powraca \"do swoich\", do ma\u0142ej wioski na kresach, tak motywuj\u0105c sw\u0105 decyzj\u0119: \"Nie dom\u00f3w mi potrzeba i pa\u0142ac\u00f3w, ale tego serca, kt\u00f3rego tam, w wielkim \u015bwiecie, nie znalaz\u0142em, ale tej dobroci, kt\u00f3rej mi nie dali\".", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1422888740i/2161329.jpg", "genres": ["Historical Fiction", "Romance", "Polish Literature", "Classic Literature", "Audiobook", "Literature", "Classics", "Drama", "Fiction", "20th Century"], "isbn": "8371801203", "isbn13": "9788371801204", "publisher": "Pr\u00f3szy\u0144ski i S-ka", "series": ["Znachor"], "author": ["Tadeusz Do\u0142\u0119ga-Mostowicz"], "publishDate": 820483200000, "places": ["Poland"], "ratingHistogram": [5, 46, 239, 575, 886], "ratingsCount": 1751, "reviewsCount": 103, "numPages": 404, "language": "Polish"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/332613.One_Flew_Over_the_Cuckoo_s_Nest", "title": "One Flew Over the Cuckoo\u2019s Nest", "titleComplete": "One Flew Over the Cuckoo\u2019s Nest", "description": "Alternate cover edition of ISBN 9780451163967Tyrannical Nurse Ratched rules her ward in an Oregon State mental hospital with a strict and unbending routine, unopposed by her patients, who remain cowed by mind-numbing medication and the threat of electric shock therapy. But her regime is disrupted by the arrival of McMurphy \u2013 the swaggering, fun-loving trickster with a devilish grin who resolves to oppose her rules on behalf of his fellow inmates. His struggle is seen through the eyes of Chief Bromden, a seemingly mute half-Indian patient who understands McMurphy's heroic attempt to do battle with the powers that keep them imprisoned. Ken Kesey's extraordinary first novel is an exuberant, ribald and devastatingly honest portrayal of the boundaries between sanity and madness.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1516211014i/332613.jpg", "genres": ["Psychology", "Literary Fiction", "Novels", "School", "Mental Illness", "Literature", "Mental Health", "Classics", "American", "Fiction"], "publisher": "Signet", "author": ["Ken Kesey"], "publishDate": -218217600000, "characters": ["Chief Bromden", "Charles Cheswick", "William \"Billy\" Bibbit", "Bruce Fredrickson", "Scanlon", "Nurse Ratched", "Martini", "Randle Patrick McMurphy", "Dale Harding", "James \"Jim\" Sefelt", "Doctor Spivey"], "places": ["Oregon", "The United States of America", "Salem, Oregon"], "ratingHistogram": [8303, 22764, 108038, 267872, 323185], "ratingsCount": 730162, "reviewsCount": 15867, "numPages": 325, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10629.Christine", "title": "Christine", "titleComplete": "Christine", "description": "Christine est belle, rac\u00e9e, s\u00e9duisante.Elle aime les sensations fortes, les vir\u00e9es nocturnes et le rock n'roll des ann\u00e9es h\u00e9ro\u00efques. Depuis qu'elle conna\u00eet Arnie, elle est amoureuse. Signe particulier : Christine est une Plymouth \u00ab Fury \u00bb, sortie en 1958 des ateliers automobiles de Detroit.Une seule rivale en travers de sa route : Leigh, la petite amie d'Arnie\u2026Ce roman l\u00e9gendaire de Stephen King, rythm\u00e9 par la musique de Chuck Berry et de Janis Joplin, a d\u00e9j\u00e0 pris place parmi les classiques de l'\u00e9pouvante.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1663053062i/10629.jpg", "genres": ["Mystery", "Adult", "Fantasy", "Thriller", "Supernatural", "Audiobook", "Fiction", "Paranormal", "Suspense", "Horror"], "asin": "2253147699", "isbn": "2253147699", "isbn13": "9782253147695", "publisher": "LGF", "author": ["Marie Milpois", "Stephen King"], "publishDate": 992415600000, "characters": ["Leigh Cabot", "Arnie Cunningham", "Dennis Guilder"], "places": ["Pennsylvania"], "ratingHistogram": [4446, 17704, 65345, 78141, 75294], "ratingsCount": 240930, "reviewsCount": 5262, "numPages": 411, "language": "French", "awards": [{"name": "Locus Award", "awardedAt": 441792000000, "category": "Best Fantasy Novel", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/105711.The_Big_Sleep_and_Other_Novels", "title": "The Big Sleep  and Other Novels", "titleComplete": "The Big Sleep  and Other Novels (Philip Marlowe #1-2, 6)", "description": "Raymond Chandler created the fast talking, trouble seeking Californian private eye Philip Marlowe for his first great novel 'The Big Sleep' in 1939. Marlowe's entanglement with the Sternwood family - and an attendant cast of colourful underworld figures - is the background to a story reflecting all the tarnished glitter of the great American Dream. The detective's iconic image burns just as brightly in 'Farewell My Lovely', on the trail of a missing nightclub crooner. And the inimitable Marlowe is able to prove that trouble really is his business in Raymond Chandler's brilliant epitaph, 'The Long Goodbye'.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1329934680i/105711.jpg", "genres": ["Crime", "Fiction", "Modern Classics", "Thriller", "Noir", "Classics", "American", "Mystery", "20th Century", "Detective"], "asin": "014118261X", "isbn": "014118261X", "isbn13": "9780141182612", "publisher": "Penguin", "series": ["Philip Marlowe"], "author": ["Raymond Chandler"], "publishDate": 949564800000, "ratingHistogram": [36, 79, 387, 1024, 1659], "ratingsCount": 3185, "reviewsCount": 84, "numPages": 672, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10625.Dolores_Claiborne", "title": "Dolores Claiborne", "titleComplete": "Dolores Claiborne", "description": "\u00c0 Little Tall, on ne sais toujours pas exactement ce qui s'est pass\u00e9 il y a trente ans, et si l'accident qui, le jour de l'\u00e9clipse, a co\u00fbt\u00e9 la vie au mari de Dolores Claiborne \u00e9tait vraiment un accident...Aujourd'hui, la vieille dame indigne est \u00e0 nouveau soup\u00e7onn\u00e9e : la riche et s\u00e9nile Vera Donovan, dont elle est la gouvernante depuis des d\u00e9cennies, vient d'\u00eatre d\u00e9couverte morte dans sa demeure.Seul t\u00e9moin et seule h\u00e9riti\u00e8re, Dolores fait figure de coupable id\u00e9ale. Elle n'a d\u00e9sormais plus le choix : elle doit passer aux aveux. Raconter les \u00e9tranges phobies qui habitaient sa ma\u00eetresse, se souvenir de l'horreur qu'elle a v\u00e9cu il y a trente ans. Dire toute la v\u00e9rit\u00e9 : une v\u00e9rit\u00e9 terrifiante.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1394213480i/10625.jpg", "genres": ["Crime", "Fiction", "Adult", "Thriller", "Audiobook", "Mystery Thriller", "Drama", "Mystery", "Suspense", "Horror"], "asin": "2266047426", "isbn": "2266047426", "isbn13": "9782266047425", "publisher": "Pocket", "author": ["Stephen King", "Dominique Dill"], "publishDate": 847267200000, "places": ["Little Tall Island"], "ratingHistogram": [2080, 9182, 37148, 54411, 49695], "ratingsCount": 152516, "reviewsCount": 5040, "numPages": 324, "language": "French"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10583.Pet_Sematary", "title": "Pet Sematary", "titleComplete": "Pet Sematary", "description": "The house looked right, felt right, to Dr Louis Creed. Rambling, old, unsmart and comfortable. A place where the family could settle; the children grow and play and explore. The rolling hills and meadows of Maine seemed a world away from the fume-choked dangers of Chicago.Only the occasional big truck out on the two-lane highway, grinding up through the gears, hammering down the long gradients, growled out an intrusive note of threat.But behind the house and away from the road: that was safe. Just a carefully clear path up into the woods where generations of local children have processed with the solemn innocence of the young, taking with them their dear departed pets for burial.A sad place maybe, but safe. Surely a safe place. Not a place to seep into your dreams, to wake you, sweating with fear and foreboding...", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1308894674i/10583.jpg", "genres": ["Adult", "Mystery", "Fantasy", "Thriller", "Supernatural", "Audiobook", "Fiction", "Paranormal", "Suspense", "Horror"], "asin": "1416524347", "isbn": "1416524347", "isbn13": "9781416524342", "publisher": "Pocket", "author": ["Stephen King"], "publishDate": 1125558000000, "characters": ["Rachel Creed", "Jud Crandall", "Gage Creed", "Victor Pascow", "Louis Creed", "Ellie Creed"], "places": ["Ludlow, Maine", "Maine"], "ratingHistogram": [7477, 26036, 117207, 210299, 226519], "ratingsCount": 587538, "reviewsCount": 23931, "numPages": 576, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Locus Award", "awardedAt": 441792000000, "category": "Best Fantasy Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "World Fantasy Award", "awardedAt": 441792000000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}]}
