{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/107291.Needful_Things", "title": "Needful Things", "titleComplete": "Needful Things", "description": "Leland Gaunt opens a new shop in Castle Rock called Needful Things. Anyone who enters his store finds the object of his or her lifelong dreams and desires: a prized baseball card, a healing amulet. In addition to a token payment, Gaunt requests that each person perform a little \"deed,\" usually a seemingly innocent prank played on someone else from town. These practical jokes cascade out of control and soon the entire town is doing battle with itself. Only Sheriff Alan Pangborn suspects that Gaunt is behind the population's increasingly violent behavior.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1315767817i/107291.jpg", "genres": ["Mystery", "Adult", "Fantasy", "Thriller", "Supernatural", "Audiobook", "Fiction", "Paranormal", "Suspense", "Horror"], "publisher": "Hodder & Stoughton Ltd", "author": ["Stephen King"], "publishDate": 694252800000, "characters": ["George T. Nelson", "Leland Gaunt", "Brian Rusk", "Sally Ratcliffe", "Cora Rusk", "Alan Pangborn", "Norris Ridgewick", "Seaton Thomas", "Ace Merrill", "Frank Jewett", "Hugh Priest", "Sean Rusk", "Slopey Dodd", "Danforth Keeton", "Henry Beaufort", "Lester Pratt", "Netitia Cobb", "Myrtle Keeton", "Wilma Jerzyck", "Polly Chalmers", "Henry Payton"], "places": ["Castle Rock, Maine", "Maine"], "ratingHistogram": [3300, 13247, 58477, 89672, 86481], "ratingsCount": 251177, "reviewsCount": 6248, "numPages": 790, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10644930-11-22-63", "title": "11/22/63", "titleComplete": "11/22/63", "description": "On November 22, 1963, three shots rang out in Dallas, President Kennedy died, and the world changed. Unless...In 2011, Jake Epping, an English teacher from Lisbon Falls, Maine, sets out on an insane \u2014 and insanely possible \u2014 mission to prevent the Kennedy assassination.Leaving behind a world of computers and mobile phones, he goes back to a time of big American cars and diners, of Lindy Hopping, the sound of Elvis, and the taste of root beer.In this haunting world, Jake falls in love with Sadie, a beautiful high school librarian. And, as the ominous date of 11/22/63 approaches, he encounters a troubled loner named Lee Harvey Oswald...", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327876792i/10644930.jpg", "genres": ["Mystery", "Science Fiction", "Historical Fiction", "Fantasy", "Thriller", "Time Travel", "Audiobook", "Fiction", "Historical", "Horror"], "asin": "1451627289", "isbn": "1451627289", "isbn13": "9781451627282", "publisher": "Scribner", "author": ["Stephen King"], "publishDate": 1320739200000, "characters": ["Lee Harvey Oswald", "Beverly Marsh", "Al Templeton", "Bill Titus", "Sadie Dunhill", "Yellow Card Man", "John F. Kennedy", "Ellen Dockerty", "George de Mohrenschildt", "Deacon \"Deke\" Simmons", "Harry Dunning", "Richie Tozier", "Jake Epping", "Marina Oswald Porter"], "places": ["Jodie, Texas", "Maine", "Derry, Maine"], "ratingHistogram": [5199, 12760, 57794, 183324, 277963], "ratingsCount": 537040, "reviewsCount": 47638, "numPages": 849, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Locus Award", "awardedAt": 1325404800000, "category": "Best SF Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "World Fantasy Award", "awardedAt": 1325404800000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "ITW Thriller Award", "awardedAt": 1325404800000, "category": "Best Hard Cover Nov