{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/32692.Gerald_s_Game", "title": "Gerald's Game", "titleComplete": "Gerald's Game", "description": "A game. A husband-and-wife game. Gerald's Game.But this time Jessie didn't want to play. Lying there, spreadeagled and handcuffed to the bedstead while he'd loomed and drooled over her, she'd felt angry and humiliated.So she'd kicked out hard. Aimed to hit him where it hurt.And now he was dead - a coronary - on the floor.Leaving Jessie alone and helpless in a lakeside holiday cabin. Miles from nowhere. No-one to hear her screams.Alone. Except for the voices in her head that begun to chatter and argue and sneer...", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1297737756i/32692.jpg", "genres": ["Fiction", "Adult", "Novels", "Thriller", "Fantasy", "Audiobook", "Mystery Thriller", "Mystery", "Suspense", "Horror"], "asin": "0831727527", "isbn": "0831727527", "isbn13": "9780831727529", "publisher": "Smithmark Publishers", "author": ["Stephen King"], "publishDate": 757411200000, "characters": ["Ruth Neary", "Jessie Mahout Burlingame", "Gerald Burlingame"], "ratingHistogram": [7479, 18607, 48333, 48763, 38582], "ratingsCount": 161764, "reviewsCount": 6003, "numPages": 332, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/140278.4", "title": "4:50 from Paddington", "titleComplete": "4:50 from Paddington (Miss Marple, #8)", "description": "For an instant the two trains ran together, going in the same direction side by side. In that frozen moment, Elspeth, riding in the one train, witnessed a murder in the other. Helplessly, she stared out her carriage window as a man remorselessly tightened his grip around a woman\u2019s throat. The body crumpled. Then the other train drew away.Who, apart from Miss Marple, would take her story seriously? After all, there were no suspects, no other witnesses... and no corpse. Not the police.Librarian's note: this entry is for the novel, \"4:50 from Paddington.\" Collections and other Miss Marple stories are located elsewhere on Goodreads. The series includes 12 novels and 20 short stories. Entries for the short stories can be found by searching Goodreads for: \"a Miss Marple Short Story.\"", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388324483i/140278.jpg", "genres": ["Crime", "Fiction", "British Literature", "Thriller", "Murder Mystery", "Audiobook", "Mystery Thriller", "Classics", "Mystery", "Detective"], "asin": "1579126936", "isbn": "1579126936", "isbn13": "9781579126933", "publisher": "Black Dog & Leventhal Publishers", "series": ["Miss Marple"], "author": ["Agatha Christie"], "publishDate": 1175238000000, "characters": ["Luther Crackenthorpe", "Emma Crackenthorpe", "Madame Joilet", "Alexander Eastley", "Edmund Crackenthorpe", "Mr. Wimborne", "Dermot Craddock", "Bryan Eastley", "Frank Cornish", "Lucy Eyelesbarrow", "James Stoddart-West", "Alfred Crackenthorpe", "Miss Marple", "Cedric Crackenthorpe", "Anna Stravinska", "Mrs. Kidder", "Martine Dubois", "Armand Dessin", "Elspeth McGillicuddy", "Inspector Bacon", "Dr. Quimper", "Dr. Morris (4:50 from Paddington)", "Harold Crackenthorpe"], "places": ["Brackhampton", "St. Mary Mead, England", "Paris"], 