{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/51496.Dr_Jekyll_and_Mr_Hyde", "title": "Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde", "titleComplete": "Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde", "description": "Robert Louis Stevenson's masterpiece of the duality of good and evil in man's nature sprang from the darkest recesses of his own unconscious\u2014during a nightmare from which his wife awakened him, alerted by his screams. More than a hundred years later, this tale of the mild-mannered Dr. Jekyll and the drug that unleashes his evil, inner persona\u2014the loathsome, twisted Mr. Hyde\u2014has lost none of its ability to shock. Its realistic police-style narrative chillingly relates Jekyll's desperation as Hyde gains control of his soul\u2014and gives voice to our own fears of the violence and evil within us. Written before Freud's naming of the ego and the id, Stevenson's enduring classic demonstrates a remarkable understanding of the personality's inner conflicts\u2014and remains the irresistibly terrifying stuff of our worst nightmares.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1318116526i/51496.jpg", "genres": ["Science Fiction", "School", "19th Century", "Fantasy", "Gothic", "Literature", "Audiobook", "Classics", "Mystery", "Horror"], "asin": "0451528956", "isbn": "0451528956", "isbn13": "9780451528957", "publisher": "Signet Classic", "author": ["Jerome Charyn", "Vladimir Nabokov", "Dan Chaon", "Simon Vestdijk", "Robert Louis Stevenson"], "publishDate": 1062486000000, "characters": ["Mr Edward Hyde", "Dr Henry Jekyll", "Richard Enfield", "Mr Gabriel John Utterson", "Poole (Jekyll & Hyde)", "Dr Hastie Lanyon"], "places": ["London, England", "United Kingdom", "England"], "ratingHistogram": [7342, 33328, 159853, 223897, 151309], "ratingsCount": 575729, "reviewsCount": 22634, "numPages": 139, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Independent Publisher Book Award (IPPY)", "awardedAt": 915177600000, "category": "Audio Fiction - Abridged