{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/11566.The_Green_Mile", "title": "The Green Mile", "titleComplete": "The Green Mile", "description": "At Cold Mountain Penitentiary, along the lonely stretch of cells known as the Green Mile, condemned killers such as 'Billy the Kid' Wharton and the possessed Eduard Delacroix await death strapped in 'Old Sparky'. But good or evil, innocent or guilty, prisoner or guard, none has ever seen the brutal likes of the new prisoner, John Coffey, sentenced to death for raping and murdering two young girls. Is Coffey a devil in human form? Or is he a far, far different kind of being?There are more wonders in heaven and hell than anyone at Cold Mountain can imagine and one of those wonders might just have stepped in amongst them.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1373903563i/11566.jpg", "genres": ["Crime", "Fiction", "Historical Fiction", "Fantasy", "Thriller", "Supernatural", "Classics", "Mystery", "Paranormal", "Horror"], "asin": "0451933028", "isbn": "0451933028", "isbn13": "9780451933027", "publisher": "Penguin Signet", "series": ["The Green Mile"], "author": ["Stephen King"], "publishDate": 843721200000, "characters": ["Percy Wetmore", "Brutus Howell", "John Coffey", "Paul Edgecomb", "American Law Enforcement"], "places": ["Louisiana, United States"], "ratingHistogram": [1312, 4365, 27618, 93203, 191772], "ratingsCount": 318270, "reviewsCount": 12656, "numPages": 592, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Bram Stoker Award", "awardedAt": 820483200000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Audie Award", "awardedAt": 852105600000, "category": "Fiction, Unabridged", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/890.Of_Mice_and_Men", "title": "Of Mice and Men", "titleComplete": "Of Mice and Men", "description": "\n  \u201cI got you to look after me, and you got me to look after you, and that's why.\u201d\nThey are an unlikely pair: George is \"small and quick and dark of face\"; Lennie, a man of tremendous size, has the mind of a young child. Yet they have formed a \"family,\" clinging together in the face of loneliness and alienation. Laborers in California's dusty vegetable fields, they hustle work when they can, living a hand-to-mouth existence. But George and Lennie have a plan: to own an acre of land and a shack they can call their own.While the powerlessness of the laboring class is a recurring theme in Steinbeck's work of the late 1930s, he narrowed his focus when composing Of Mice and Men, creating an intimate portrait of two men facing a world marked by petty tyranny, misunderstanding, jealousy, and callousness. But though the scope is narrow, the theme is universal: a friendship and a shared dream that makes an individual's existence meaningful.A unique perspective on life's hardships, this story has achieved the status of timeless classic due to its remarkable success as a novel, a Broadway play, and three acclaimed films.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1511302904i/890.jpg", "genres": ["High School", "School", "Novels", "Historical Fiction", "Literature", "Classics", "American", "Fiction", "Historical", "Read For School"], "asin": "0142000671", "isbn": "0142000671", "isbn13": "9780142000670", "publisher": "Penguin Books", "author": ["John Steinbeck"], "publishDate": 1009872000000, "characters": ["Curley", "Candy", "Whit", "George Milton", "Crooks", "Carlson", "Slim", "Lennie Small", "Curley's Wife"], "places": ["California", "Salinas Valley, California"], "ratingHistogram": [70802, 171702, 569784, 886331, 832646], "ratingsCount": 2531265, "reviewsCou