{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/333867.The_Stars_My_Destination", "title": "The Stars My Destination", "titleComplete": "The Stars My Destination", "description": "In this pulse-quickening novel, Alfred Bester imagines a future in which people \"jaunte\" a thousand miles with a single thought, where the rich barricade themselves in labyrinths and protect themselves with radioactive hitmen\u2014and where an inarticulate outcast is the most valuable and dangerous man alive. The Stars My Destination is a classic of technological prophecy and timeless narrative enchantment by an acknowledged master of science fiction.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1433671750i/333867.jpg", "genres": ["Science Fiction Fantasy", "Science Fiction", "Novels", "Space Opera", "Fantasy", "Classics", "Cyberpunk", "Fiction", "Space", "Speculative Fiction"], "asin": "0679767800", "isbn": "0679767800", "isbn13": "9780679767800", "publisher": "Vintage", "author": ["Alfred Bester"], "publishDate": 836290800000, "characters": ["Robin Wednesbury", "Saul Dagenham", "Sam Quatt", "Regis Sheffield", "Presteign", "Gulliver Foyle", "Jisbella McQueen"], "ratingHistogram": [833, 2497, 9394, 18041, 20334], "ratingsCount": 51099, "reviewsCount": 3590, "numPages": 258, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Prometheus Hall of Fame Award", "awardedAt": 568022400000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}]}
