{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/89723.The_Lottery_and_Other_Stories", "title": "The Lottery and Other Stories", "titleComplete": "The Lottery and Other Stories", "description": "The Lottery, one of the most terrifying stories written in this century, created a sensation when it was first published in The New Yorker. \"Power and haunting,\" and \"nights of unrest\" were typical reader responses. This collection, the only one to appear during Shirley Jackson's lifetime, unites \"The Lottery:\" with twenty-four equally unusual stories. Together they demonstrate Jackson's remarkable range--from the hilarious to the truly horrible--and power as a storyteller.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1416448200i/89723.jpg", "genres": ["Adult", "Anthologies", "Short Stories", "Gothic", "Literature", "Audiobook", "Classics", "American", "Fiction", "Horror"], "asin": "0374529531", "isbn": "0374529531", "isbn13": "9780374529536", "publisher": "Farrar, Straus and Giroux", "author": ["Shirley Jackson", "A.M. Homes"], "publishDate": 1110960000000, "ratingHistogram": [980, 3462, 15490, 29390, 27915], "ratingsCount": 77237, "reviewsCount": 4011, "numPages": 302, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/15759648-mantaua-nasul-nsemn-rile-unui-nebun", "title": "Mantaua. Nasul. \u00censemn\u0103rile unui nebun", "titleComplete": "Mantaua. Nasul. \u00censemn\u0103rile unui nebun", "description": "Fie ca este un frizer ticait, cicalit de nevasta, pe care il loveste nenorocirea din pricina unui nas gasit in piine, sau un functionar a carui pasiune pentru litere e pe atit de mare, pe cit de mica-i este averea pe care si-o cheltuie pe-o manta, eroul povestirilor lui Gogol este in toate numai excese: simte enorm, vede monstruos si totul ii este peste poate. Veselia pe care o nasc intimplarile lui este, cum o spune chiar Gogol, rodul unor accese \u201einexplicabile chiar pentru mine insumi, care proveneau probabil chiar din starea mea bolnavicioasa. Ca sa ma distrez, nascoceam toate lucrurile comice de care eram in stare\u201d.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1342697056i/15759648.jpg", "genres": ["Russia", "19th Century", "Short Stories", "Classic Literature", "Literature", "Classics", "Fiction", "Russian Literature"], "asin": "9734624024", "isbn": "9734624024", "isbn13": "9789734624027", "publisher": "Polirom", "author": ["Emil Iordache", "Nikolai Gogol"], "publishDate": 1325404800000, "ratingHistogram": [5, 19, 164, 284, 283], "ratingsCount": 755, "reviewsCount": 37, "numPages": 156, "language": "Romanian"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/254308.Oblomov", "title": "Oblomov", "titleComplete": "Oblomov", "description": "Even though Ivan Goncharov wrote several books that were widely read and discussed during his lifetime, today he is remembered for one novel, Oblomov, published in 1859, an indisputable classic of Russian literature, the artistic stature and cultural significance of which may be compared only to other such masterpieces as Nikolai Gogol's Dead Souls, Leo Tolstoy's Anna Karenina, and Fyodor Dostoevsky's Brothers Karamazov. Stephen Pearl's new translation, the first major English-language publication of Oblomov in more than fifty years, succeeds exquisitely to introduce this astonishing and endearing novel to a new generation of readers.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1635452768i/254308.jpg", "genres": ["Russia", "19th Century", "Novels", "Historical Fiction", "Roman", "Literature", "Classics", "Humor", "Fiction", "Russian Literature"], "asin": "1933480092", "isbn": "1933480092", "isbn13": "9781933480091", "publisher": "Bunim & Bannigan Ltd", "author": ["Ivan Goncharov", "Stephen Pearl", "Galya Diment"], "publishDate": 1160636400000, "ratingHistogram": [691, 1862, 6338, 12783, 16778], "ratingsCount": 38452, "reviewsCount": 1837, "numPages": 586, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "AATSEEL Book Prize", "awardedAt": 1199174400000, "category": "Best Translation into English", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7629.The_Good_Soldier_vejk", "title": "The Good Soldier \u0160vejk", "titleComplete": "The Good Soldier \u0160vejk", "description": "In The Good Soldier \u0160vejk, celebrated Czech writer and anarchist Jaroslav Ha\u0161ek combined dazzling wordplay and piercing satire in a hilariously subversive depiction of the futility of war.Good-natured and garrulous, \u0160vejk becomes the Austrian army's most loyal Czech soldier when he is called up on the outbreak of World War I -- although his bumbling attempts to get to the front serve only to prevent him from reaching it. Playing cards and getting drunk, he uses all his cunning and genial subterfuge to deal with the police, clergy, and officers who chivy him toward battle.Cecil Parrott's vibrant translation conveys the brilliant irreverence of this classic about a hapless Everyman caught in a vast bureaucratic machine.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1624922804i/7629.jpg", "genres": ["World War I", "Novels", "Historical Fiction", "Czech Literature", "20th Century", "Literature", "Classics", "Humor", "Fiction", "War"], "asin": "0140449914", "publisher": "Penguin Classics", "series": ["The Fateful Adventures of the Good Soldier \u0160vejk During the World War"], "author": ["Cecil Parrott", "Josef Lada", "Jaroslav Ha\u0161ek"], "publishDate": 1135670400000, "characters": ["2nd Lieutenant Dub", "Chaplain Otto Katz", "General Fink von Finkenstein", "Captain Sagner", "Captain Tayrle", "Bretschneider", "Volunteer Marek", "Vodi\u010dka", "Chaplain Martinec", "Colonel Friedrich Kraus von Zillergut", "Jurajda", "Quartermaster Sergeant-Major Van\u011bk", "Palivec", "Cadet Biegler", "Staff Warder Slav\u00edk", "Baloun", "Lieutenant Luk\u00e1\u0161", "\"Sergeant Teveles\"", "Josef \u0160vejk", "Colonel Schr\u00f6der"], "places": ["Prague (Praha)"], "ratingHistogram": [358, 950, 3288, 6304, 8121], "ratingsCount": 19021, "re