{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18007564-the-martian", "title": "The Martian", "titleComplete": "The Martian", "description": "Six days ago, astronaut Mark Watney became one of the first people to walk on Mars. Now, he\u2019s sure he\u2019ll be the first person to die there.After a dust storm nearly kills him and forces his crew to evacuate while thinking him dead, Mark finds himself stranded and completely alone with no way to even signal Earth that he\u2019s alive\u2014and even if he could get word out, his supplies would be gone long before a rescue could arrive. Chances are, though, he won\u2019t have time to starve to death. The damaged machinery, unforgiving environment, or plain-old \u201chuman error\u201d are much more likely to kill him first. But Mark isn\u2019t ready to give up yet. Drawing on his ingenuity, his engineering skills \u2014 and a relentless, dogged refusal to quit \u2014 he steadfastly confronts one seemingly insurmountable obstacle after the next. Will his resourcefulness be enough to overcome the impossible odds against him?", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1413706054i/18007564.jpg", "genres": ["Survival", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "Adult", "Science Fiction", "Thriller", "Audiobook", "Adventure", "Humor", "Fiction", "Space"], "asin": "0804139024", "isbn": "0804139024", "isbn13": "9780804139021", "publisher": "Ballantine Books", "series": ["The Martian"], "author": ["Andy Weir"], "publishDate": 1392105600000, "characters": ["Teddy Sanders", "Alex Vogel", "Mindy Park", "Bruce Ng", "Brendan Hutch", "Venkat Kapoor", "Melissa Lewis", "Annie Montrose", "Rich Purnell", "Beth Johanssen", "Mark Watney", "Chris Beck", "Rick Martinez", "Mitch Henderson"], "places": ["Mars", "Houston, Texas"], "ratingHistogram": [9598, 22174, 99174, 348362, 634311], "ratingsCount": 1113619, "reviewsCount": 86822, "numPages": 384, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Kurd-La\u00dfw