{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/12355917-ai-toat-via-a-nainte", "title": "Ai toat\u0103 via\u0163a \u00eenainte", "titleComplete": "Ai toat\u0103 via\u0163a \u00eenainte", "description": "Un roman care te cucereste de la primele rinduri, de un umor nebun si scris cu o verva care te obliga sa nu-l lasi din mina. Povestea unui pui de arab abandonat de parinti si crescut de o evreica batrina care isi recapata energia cind se uita la portretul lui Hitler. Copilul se invirte printre prostituate, proxeneti, comercianti de doi bani si drogati, de la care invata toate lectiile cinismului, dar \u2013 printre picaturi \u2013 si lectia iubirii totale, mai puternica decit moartea mamei sale de imprumut. \u201cAi toata viata inainte\u201d este o poveste despre tandretea suferintei, spusa din perspcetiva unui copil inteligent si precoce, prea devreme familiarizat cu adevarurile oamenilor mari. In 1978, filmul \u201cLa vie devant soi\u201d, cu Simone Signoret in rolul principal, a cistigat Premiul Oscar pentru cel mai bun film strain.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1341158385i/12355917.jpg", "genres": ["France", "French Literature", "Novels", "School", "Roman", "Literature", "Classics", "Fiction", "20th Century", "Contemporary"], "isbn": "0978753224", "publisher": "Editura Univers", "author": ["Laszlo Alexandru", "Romain Gary"], "publishDate": 1136102400000, "characters": ["Momo", "Madame Rosa"], "places": ["Paris"], "ratingHistogram": [371, 1099, 4326, 10201, 13920], "ratingsCount": 29917, "reviewsCount": 2557, "numPages": 176, "language": "Romanian", "awards": [{"name": "Prix Goncourt", "awardedAt": 157795200000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"name": "\u041f\u0440\u0435\u043c\u0456\u044f \u00ab\u0421\u043a\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0430\u00bb", "awardedAt": 1230796800000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/93157.The_Monk", "title": "The Monk", "titleComplete": "The Monk", "description": "'He now saw himself stained with the most loathed and monstrous sins, the object of universal execration ... doomed to perish in tortures the most severe'Shocking, erotic and violent, The Monk is the story of Ambrosio, torn between his spiritual vows and the temptations of physical pleasure. His internal battle leads to sexual obsession, rape and murder, yet this book also contains knowing parody of its own excesses as well as social comedy. Written by Matthew Lewis when he was only nineteen, it was a ground-breaking novel in the Gothic Horror genre and spawned hundreds of imitators, drawn in by its mixture of bloodshed, sex and scandal.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1365712491i/93157.jpg", "genres": ["18th Century", "British Literature", "Novels", "Historical Fiction", "Fantasy", "Gothic", "Literature", "Classics", "Fiction", "Horror"], "asin": "0140436030", "isbn": "0140436030", "isbn13": "9780140436037", "publisher": "Penguin Classics", "author": ["Matthew Gregory Lewis"], "publishDate": 928220400000, "characters": ["Matilda", "Lorenzo", "Raymond", "Antonia Wyndham", "Agnes", "Ambrosio"], "places": ["Madrid", "Spain"], "ratingHistogram": [810, 2116, 6814, 10308, 8575], "ratingsCount": 28623, "reviewsCount": 2670, "numPages": 431, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/41811.The_Caves_of_Steel", "title": "The Caves of Steel", "titleComplete": "The Caves of Steel (Robot, #1)", "description": "A millennium into the future two advancements have altered the course of human history: the colonization of the galaxy and the creation of the positronic brain. Isaac Asimov's Robot novels chronicle the unlikely partnership between a New York City detective and a humanoid robot who must learn to work together. Like most people left behind on an over-populated Earth, New York City police detective Elijah Baley had little love for either the arrogant Spacers or their robotic companions. But when a prominent Spacer is murdered under mysterious circumstances, Baley is ordered to the Outer Worlds to help track down the killer. The relationship between Life and his Spacer superiors, who distrusted all Earthmen, was strained from the start. Then he learned that they had assigned him a partner: R. Daneel Olivaw. Worst of all was that the \"R\" stood for robot--and his positronic partner was made in the image and likeness of the murder victim!", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1335782224i/41811.jpg", "genres": ["Crime", "Fiction", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "Science Fiction", "Novels", "Robots", "Audiobook", "Classics", "Mystery", "Detective"], "publisher": "Voyager", "series": ["Robot, chronological order", "Greater Foundation Universe", "Robot"], "author": ["Isaac Asimov"], "publishDate": 852105600000, "characters": ["Elijah Baley", "R. Daneel Olivaw"], "ratingHistogram": [390, 2052, 16471, 40516, 40606], "ratingsCount": 100035, "reviewsCount": 3909, "numPages": 206, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Retro Hugo Award", "awardedAt": 1072944000000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/30016.The_Naked_Sun", "title": "The Naked Sun", "titleComplete": "The Naked Sun (Robot, #2)", "description": "Like all Earthmen, detective Elijah Baley has a terror of open landscape., of the naked sun.Reacting in fear of the technological superiority of the Outer Worlds, the people of Earth have hidden themselves in vast underground cities, nursing a hatred for Spacers. The fifty Outer Worlds of the Spacers together are home to fewer people than planet Earth. And home to many, many more robots. Earthmen hate Spacer robots, too...But Baley doesn't. He once had a robot partner, R. Daneel \u2013 and when the authorities of the planet Solaria request terrestrial assistance in investigating a murder, Baley is once again teamed with Daneel. He is the first Earthmen in a millennium to travel to the Outer Worlds... and he must endure the glare of a sun far more deadly than Earth's.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1655932374i/30016.jpg", "genres": ["Crime", "Fiction", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "Science Fiction", "Novels", "Robots", "Audiobook", "Classics", "Mystery", "Detective"], "publisher": "HarperCollins Publishers", "series": ["Robot, chronological order", "Greater Foundation Universe", "Robot"], "author": ["Isaac Asimov", "Chris     Moore"], "publishDate": 725875200000, "characters": ["Gladia Delmarre", "Elijah Baley", "R. Daneel Olivaw"], "ratingHistogram": [213, 1039, 8969, 24139, 22204], "ratingsCount": 56564, "reviewsCount": 2228, "numPages": 204, "language": "English"}
