{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/153747.Moby_Dick_or_The_Whale", "title": "Moby-Dick or, The Whale", "titleComplete": "Moby-Dick or, The Whale", "description": "\"It is the horrible texture of a fabric that should be woven of ships' cables and hawsers. A Polar wind blows through it, and birds of prey hover over it.\" So Melville wrote of his masterpiece, one of the greatest works of imagination in literary history. In part, Moby-Dick is the story of an eerily compelling madman pursuing an unholy war against a creature as vast and dangerous and unknowable as the sea itself. But more than just a novel of adventure, more than an encyclopaedia of whaling lore and legend, the book can be seen as part of its author's lifelong meditation on America. Written with wonderfully redemptive humour, Moby-Dick is also a profound inquiry into character, faith, and the nature of perception.This edition of Moby-Dick, which reproduces the definitive text of the novel, includes invaluable explanatory notes, along with maps, illustrations, and a glossary of nautical terms.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327940656i/153747.jpg", "genres": ["Novels", "19th Century", "Historical Fiction", "Literature", "Classic Literature", "Audiobook", "Adventure", "Classics", "American", "Fiction"], "asin": "0142437247", "isbn": "0142437247", "isbn13": "9780142437247", "publisher": "Penguin Classics ", "author": ["Andrew Delbanco", "Anton Lomaev", "Herman Melville", "Tom Quirk", "Rockwell Kent", "William Hootkins"], "publishDate": 1045814400000, "characters": ["Perth", "Tashtego", "Stubb", "Elijah", "Fedallah", "Aunt Charity", "Fleece", "Dough-boy", "Pippin (\"Pip\")", "Flask", "Peleg", "Mrs Hussey", "Moby Dick", "Peter Coffin", "Ishmael", "Queequeg", "Captain Ahab", "Daggoo", "Mapple Priest", "Starbuck", "Bildad"], "places": ["New Bedford, Massachusetts", "New England", "Atlantic Ocean", "Massachusetts", "Pacific Ocean", "